
[1]reconcilement

   RECONCI'LEMENT, n.

   1. Reconciliation; renewal of friendship. Animosities sometimes make
   reconcilement impracticable.

   2. Friendship renewed.

   No cloud of anger shall remain, but peace assured and reconcilement.
